$templateCache.put("views/content/electrical-home.html","<section class=bg-grediant><div class=container><div class=hp-top-banner><img src=img/hp-en-pr1.jpg alt=\"Hindustan Platinum\" class=img-responsive></div></div></section><section><div class=container><div class=row><div class=col-md-12><div class=\"hp-pr-decs pd45\"><p>Hindustan Platinum is the pioneer in manufacturing of electrical contacts in India, with customer base spread across six continents. We manufacture electrical contacts for various applications such as switchgear & control gear, automotive, railways, elevators, telecom, aviation, medical, defence etc. We ensure stringent quality parameters at every stage of manufacturing process to deliver quality products to our customers. This has changed the perception about India from being a part of LCR (Low cost region) to HQR (High quality region).</p><p>Hindustan Platinum has a committed team of professionals, who understand customer needs. We have a dedicated team for research & development to create value for our customers. We have been continuously investing in equipments with latest technologies from across the globe to meet ever increasing customer demand, while simultaneously deploying Lean Manufacturing Concepts in Contacts division. The entire manufacturing process is conducted in-house....from refining of precious metal to final manufacturing of products, tailor made as per customer requirement. We provide RoHS & REACH assistance to our customers. We are green channel suppliers to many of our esteemed customers. We manufacture various alloys which are available in different forms.</p></div></div></div><div class=hp-pr-pics><div class=row><div class=\"col-md-4 padding0\" ng-repeat=\"item in product track by $index\"><div product=\"\" value=item></div></div></div><div class=row><div class=col-md-12><div class=\"hp-cl-title text-center hp-list my-li\"><h2 class=\"color-primary font-bold\">We are ISO Certified</h2><ul class=pl12><li><a href=img/electrical/ISO9001.pdf target=_blank><img src=img/electrical/1.jpg alt=\"Hindustan Platinum\"></a></li><li><a href=img/electrical/ISO14001.pdf target=_blank><img src=img/electrical/2.jpg alt=\"Hindustan Platinum\"></a></li><li><a href=img/electrical/ISO18001.pdf target=_blank><img src=img/electrical/3.jpg alt=\"Hindustan Platinum\"></a></li><li><a href=img/electrical/SKMBT_C45114070809420.pdf target=_blank><img src=img/electrical/4.jpg alt=\"Hindustan Platinum\"></a></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><section><div class=hp-get-sec><div class=container><div class=row><div class=col-md-12><div class=\"text-center p20\"><h1 class=\"color-primary font-bold\">GET IN TOUCH</h1><div class=hp-gt><div class=\"if-no-slider hp-list p20\"><ul class=padding0><li ng-repeat=\"s in get track by $index\"><div class=hp-cn><h3 class=\"text-up font-bold margin0\">{{s.name}}</h3><p>or info related queries email</p><p>us on <a>{{s.email}}</a></p></div></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></section>");
$templateCache.put("views/content/electrodes.html","<section class=bg-grediant><div class=container><div class=hp-top-banner><img src=img/hp-electro.jpg alt=\"Hindustan Platinum\" class=img-responsive></div></div></section><section class=pb60><div class=container><div class=row><div class=col-md-12><div class=\"hp-pr-decs pd45\"><p>Platinum electrodes have an increasing demand since electrochemical methods of analysis have proved to be more economical, speedy and accurate.</p><p>Apart from the electrodes illustrated in this section, there is a wide range of electrodes to suit different purposes. Electrodes of different dimensions can also be manufactured as per the specifications.</p><p>Wire gauze cylinders for electrodes are the best as they provide larger surface area than an equal weight of plain or perforated sheet. However, if desired, we can manufacture electrodes having plain or perforated sheet cylinders. Generally these electrodes are manufactured from Platinum/10% Iridium alloy. We undertake re-processing of worn-out electrodes also.</p></div></div></div><div class=row><div class=col-md-12><div class=\"hp-tab-btn text-center\"><div class=btn-group><button type=button name=button ng-click=\"tabchanges(\'az\',1)\" class=\"{{classp}} btn-blue font-bold text-up\">Fischer Electrodes</button> <button type=button name=button ng-click=\"tabchanges(\'bz\',2)\" class=\"{{classv}} btn-blue font-bold text-up\">Platinum electrodes</button> <button type=button name=button ng-click=\"tabchanges(\'cz\',3)\" class=\"{{classq}} btn-blue font-bold text-up\">CATHODES</button></div></div></div></div><div class=az ng-if=\"tabs==\'az\'\"><div class=row><div class=\"col-md-offset-1 col-md-10\"><div class=hp-pr-decs><p>Following types of electrodes are known as “Fischer Electrodes”. These electrodes are most commonly used in laboratories for electrochemical analysis. The stems of cathode and anode are supplied in either round or square wire and can be straight or cranked as shown with or without rings. The helical anode made from round wire is used when no anodic deposition or less than 0.2% lead as lead peroxide is required.</p></div><div class=\"hp-tbl-en b-all mt60\"><img src=img/electrode-1.jpg class=img-responsive></div><div class=\"row mt60\"><div class=col-md-4 ng-repeat=\"s in shape track by $index\"><div class=hp-el-box><img src={{s}} alt=\"Hindustan Platinum\" class=img-responsive></div></div></div></div></div><div class=row><div class=\"col-md-offset-1 col-md-10\"><span class=\"font-bold hp-span\">Other sizes available on request.</span></div></div></div><div class=az ng-if=\"tabs==\'bz\'\"><div class=row><div class=\"col-md-offset-1 col-md-10\"><div class=hp-pr-decs><p>Illustrated here are similar to the heavy Fischer type. The cathode has straight stem and has no rings over it. These electrodes can be used for both stirred and unstirred solutions. When no anodic deposition is required, helix made of round wire is put to use which is comparatively less costly than that of wire gauze anode.</p></div><div class=\"hp-tbl-en b-all mt60\"><img src=img/electrode-2.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div></div><div class=az ng-if=\"tabs==\'cz\'\"><div class=row><div class=\"col-md-offset-1 col-md-10\"><div class=hp-pr-decs><p>These cathodes too can be used for both stirred and unstirred solutions and can be employed with round wire helical or paddle type electrode.</p></div><div class=\"hp-tbl-en b-all mt60\"><img src=img/electrode-3.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div></div></div></section>");
