$templateCache.put("views/content/profile.html","<section class=bg-grediant><div class=container><div class=hp-top-banner><img src=img/hp-profile.jpg alt=\"Hindustan Platinum\" class=img-responsive></div></div></section><section><div class=container><div class=row><div class=col-md-12><div class=\"hp-pr-decs pd45\"><p>Hindustan Platinum is offering superior electrical performance solid contacts which are manufactured in a wide range of sizes. Hindustan Platinum is India’s first company to introduce the bimetal contacts in 1973. This revolutionary product, that reduces Silver content substantially, helps in lowering cost while retaining high quality.</p><p>In bimetal contact rivet, a Silver layer is metallurgically bonded to Copper base. This high strength bonding imparts better thermal & current transfer & allows customers to experience the performance of solid Silver at a price that is economically viable.</p><p>Solid & bimetal rivets are usually supplied with a solid shank, but are also available with indent or chamfered shank. Accompanying heads can be flat, radial, line or conical. These rivets are used in wiring accessories, relays, contactors etc. We are one of the few manufacturers in the world who have technology to manufacture Silver Tin Oxide & Silver Cadmium Oxide by internal oxidation (melting) as well as Powder Metallurgy (sintered).</p></div></div></div></div></section><section class=pb60><div class=container><div class=row><div class=hp-pl><h2 class=\"text-up font-bold color-primary\">alloys</h2></div><div class=col-md-12><div class=hp-acc><uib-accordion close-others=oneAtATime><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default is-open=status.open><uib-accordion-heading>Pure Silver (Pure Ag)</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>Endowed with highest electrical and thermal conductivity, it has excellent formability. When alloyed with 0.2% Nickel, a fine grain Silver is obtained with characteristics like high wear resistance, good brazibility and weldability.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/semi/PureAg-12.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>AgSnO2</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>The company is one of the few manufacturers in the world having technology to manufacture Silver Tin Oxide by both internal oxidation (melting) & by powder metallurgy (sintered). Contacts are manufactured with or without additives. Special additives keep the contact resistance stable throughout. The standard grades of contact material available are AgSno2 14 %, AgSnO2 12 % and AgSno2 10 %. It is one of the most environment friendly contact material as it does not contain any hazardous substance.</p><p>Contacts are available with a backing layer of Silver and optionally, with an additional layer of brazing alloy. Available in the form of wire, rivets, profiles and contact tips.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/AgSno2.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>Silver Nickel (AgNi)</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>AgNi is manufactured by powder metallurgy (Sintered). Its salient feature includes low mechanical wear due to higher hardness, low contact resistance almost constant throughout the life of contact, low material transfer, low burning, good arc migration and better arc extinguishing properties. It also has better anti welding property. It has good formability with Nickel upto 20 %. If this percent goes higher, formability reduces a bit, but wear resistance increases. Available in the form of wires, rivets, profiles and contact tips, Silver Nickel contacts can be welded directly.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/AgNi.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>AgZnO</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>Highly recommended when subjected to intense make and break cycles, this contact material is manufactured by blending Silver and metal oxide powder. It has a uniform distribution of particles and is characterized by a high switching life time in AC relay applications.</p><p>With excellent erosion resistance, high welding resistance and free of toxic and carcinogenic content it is widely used for applications like current limiting circuit breaker, earth leakage circuit breaker, general purpose relays, wiring accessories and switchgears(requiring breaking capacity in Ac or DC between 10 and 1000 A and 24 and 600V). It is one of the best alternatives for AgCdo.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/AgZnO.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>AgFe</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>Manufactured by blending Silver and iron powder, this material is an apt substitute for Silver Nickel. It is ideal for moving contacts in safety devices with nominal currents greater than 32 A and for relays and contactors operating between 0.5 and 20 A. This material is recommended for any switchgear using current between 0.5 and 250A & 24 and 600V.</p><p>Silver Iron is used in applications like push buttons, relays, contactors and circuit breakers.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/AgFe.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>AgCdO</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>AgCdO is manufactured by internal oxidation (Melting) or by powder metallurgy (sintered). Our specialization includes making extremely ductile wire of AgCdo 15 % which is used to manufacture Bimetal Contacts.</p><p>It\'s advantages are:<ul><li>Good arc extinguishing properties.</li><li>Low arc erosion.</li><li>Excellent anti-welding character that offers reliable protection against contact welding at higher current (higher the CdO content better the anti-welding property).</li><li>Low contact resistance.</li></ul></p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/AgCdO.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>AgCu</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>Manufactured by the melted process, it offers higher mechanical strength, greater burning resistance under most switching conditions and less material migration compared to pure Silver.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/AgCu.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>AgPd</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>Harder than fine Silver, this contact material has a higher melting point and exhibits a nobler surface. It is largely resistant to sulphur and abrasion & burning. Available in the form of wire, rivets, profiles and contact tips.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/AgPd.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>AgW/AgWc</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>These materials are manufactured by powder metallurgy. The percentage of Tungsten can vary from 50 %(AgW50) up to 80% (AgW80) & 20% (AgWc20%) to 65% (AgWc65%) for Tungsten Carbide.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/AgW-08.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>CuW</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>This material has higher burning resistance compared to pure tungsten. Copper Tungsten contacts are manufactured by sintering process. These contacts are suitable for machining.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/Cuw-11.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>AgNiC</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>This material has higher burning resistance compared to pure tungsten. Copper Tungsten contacts are manufactured by sintering process. These contacts are suitable for machining.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/AgNiC-13.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div><div uib-accordion-group=\"\" class=panel-default><uib-accordion-heading>AgWcC</uib-accordion-heading><div class=hp-dt-in><p>It is manufactured by powder metallurgy. These contacts are supplied with brazeable layer of Silver. Offered in the form of profiles, contact tips.</p><div class=\"hp-tbl-en mt20\"><img src=img/AgWcC-09.jpg class=img-responsive></div></div></div></uib-accordion></div></div></div><div class=row><h2 class=\"color-primary font-bold text-up\">plating</h2><span>Above rivets are available with Silver, Gold, Nickel, Silchrome plating.</span></div></div></section>");
$templateCache.put("views/content/r&d.html","<section class=bg-grediant><div class=container><div class=hp-top-banner><img src=img/hp-rnd.jpg alt=\"Hindustan Platinum\" class=img-responsive></div></div></section><section><div class=container><div class=row><div class=col-md-12><div class=\"hp-pr-decs pd45\"><p>Hindustan platinum has fully dedicated R & D team which continuously works on developing new contacts material and improving process efficiency. This team is supported by international professionals knowledgeable in global technological changes. Creating samples, getting customer’s approval, initiating manufacturing of the production batch, freezing the manufacturing process and handing over to production team is responsibility of R & D team. Coordination between each department is instrumental in boosting consistency and new product development in tune with customer’s demand.</p><p>We have successfully developed RoHS compliant contact material which has been found to be one of the best alternatives for Silver Cadmium Oxide contact material. We produce contact materials with or without additives, as per customer’s request.</p></div><div class=hp-rnd-slider><flex-slider flex-slide=\"s in slider track by $index\" prev-text=\"\" next-text=\"\" item-width=380 item-margin=0 animation=slide><li><a><img ng-src={{s}}></a></li></flex-slider></div></div></div></div></section>");
